# YieldSwarm Helix — Cursor Swarm Constitution

## Architecture
- Tri-solenoid: Nexus (orchestration), Helix (cross-chain yield), Shadow (arena) — `config/nexus/solenoids.yaml`
- 14-pillar elevators — `config/helix/pillars.yaml` (source of truth)
- Quadrilateral → Pentagram → 14× elevators — `src/infrastructure/odysseus-router.js` + `entropy-core.js`
- Backend integration API: port **8080** — `backend/src/server.js`

## Rules
1. Map every new module to a pillar id (1–14) in `config/helix/pillars.yaml`
2. All JSON API responses from solenoid routes should include state anchors when touching `QuadrilateralSolenoidRouter`
3. Bridge root `src/infrastructure/*` into backend via `createRequire` in `backend/src/adapters/` — do not duplicate logic
4. Tesla ingest: `POST /api/telemetry/tesla` — use `TeslaMeshEntropyCore`
5. Starlink: env `STARLINK_API_KEY` — adapter stub until live key
6. Neural mesh: 14 payloads exactly — `services/neural_mesh/elevators.py`
7. No Polsia dependency — pure Cursor + this repo + env/Vault secrets
8. Cloud credits pool: $5,408 — `config/helix/pillars.yaml` `credit_pool_usd`
9. Test before deploy: `npm run test:helix` then `npm run helix:deploy-pillars`
10. Zero placeholders in production paths — stubs must return structured `{ ok, note }` not throw

## Priority build order
contracts → sovereign-optimizer → odysseus-router → dydx-bridge → vLLM 5090 SDL → ZK entropy → neural mesh APIs
